  "body": "# Problem\nIn current implementation application will try to fetch same data if request was interrupted due any issues (app closed, connection interrupted).\n\n## Implementation\nIn https://github.com/status-im/status-go/pull/1446/ new API allows to track timestamp update for each topic and if request was interrupted we will start the next one from the last updated timestamp.\n\napp will have to call `shhext_initiateHistoryRequests` with a struct:\n\n```\ntype InitiateHistoryRequestParams struct {\nPeer string // full enode of the mail server (must be connected in advance)\nSymKeyID string // optional symkey id for encrypting request payload. if not added request will be encrypted using mail server public key\nRequests []TopicRequest\nForce bool // same as before\nTimeout time.Duration // int64 duration in nanoseconds\n}\n\ntype TopicRequest struct {\nTopic whisper.TopicType // 4 bytes\nDuration time.Duration // int64 duration in nanoseconds\n}\n```\n\nReturns list of hex encoded hashes for every request.\n\nWhen envelope is received app should notify status-go about it, with `sshext_confirmMessagesProcessed`. That accepts list of whisper.Message's.\n\nOnce signal that request is completed is received and processed all relevant envelopes it should notify status-go that request was completed with: `shhext_completeRequest(request hex)`.\n\n",
